        YOU_VE_ACQUIRED_QUITE_A_REPUTATION_THERE_IS                             = 7408,  -- You've acquired quite a reputation. There is a new mission for you to tackle.
        FIRST_SPEAK_TO_SIR_NAJI_OF_THE_MYTHRIL                                  = 7409,  -- First, speak to Sir Naji of the Mythril Musketeers at the President's Office. This mission is of great import to the welfare of our nation.
        I_SEE_YOU_VE_MADE_IT_BACK_SAFELY                                        = 7410,  -- I see you've made it back safely from your journey to Windurst and San d'Oria. This new mission should not be hard for an experienced adventurer like you.
        THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_ARE_PLANNING_AN_OFFENSIVE_ON                     = 7411,  -- The Mythril Musketeers are planning an offensive on the Quadav stronghold.
        ADVENTURERS_INCLUDING_YOURSELF_HAVE_BEEN_ASKED_TO_JOIN                  = 7412,  -- Adventurers, including yourself, have been asked to join them on this operation.
        YOU_ARE_TO_GO_MEET_IRON_EATER_ONE                                       = 7413,  -- You are to go meet Iron Eater, one of the Mythril Musketeers, to receive a full briefing.
        THE_GUSGEN_MINES_IN_THE_KONSCHTAT_HIGHLANDS_HAVE                        = 7414,  -- The Gusgen Mines in the Konschtat Highlands have been dug to the bare rock and abandoned for some time...
        BUT_LATELY_THERE_HAVE_BEEN_REPORTS_THAT_A                               = 7415,  -- But lately, there have been reports that a rare ore can be found in them. No one has claimed this new vein yet.
        YOU_ARE_TO_BRING_BACK_A_SAMPLE_OF                                       = 7416,  -- You are to bring back a sample of the ore to confirm these reports. A Galka adventurer named Davyad should be able to help you. He is said to have acquired a chunk of the ore when he was there last.
        THE_ITEM_THAT_DAVYAD_BROUGHT_BACK_WAS_THAT                              = 7417,  -- The item that Davyad brought back was %. That is what you should seek as well. Once you have the ore, hand them over to me or one of my colleagues.
        YOU_HAVE_SUCCEEDED_IN_BRINGING_BACK_GOOD_WORK                           = 7418,  -- You have succeeded in bringing back %. Good work, adventurer. This discovery may help rejuvenate Bastok's economy!
        YOU_HAVE_HEARD_OF_JEUNO_HAVE_YOU_NOT                                    = 7419,  -- You have heard of Jeuno, have you not? The Bastokan government is currently looking for someone to send there, and your name is on the list of candidates.
        THE_PRESIDENTIAL_AIDE_SIR_LUCIUS_HIMSELF_RECOMMENDED_YOU                = 7420,  -- The presidential aide, Sir Lucius himself, recommended you. It is a great honor--you should be proud!
        SIR_LUCIUS_WISHES_TO_SEE_YOU_AS_SOON                                    = 7421,  -- Sir Lucius wishes to see you as soon as possible. Go meet him in his office in the administrative section at the top of the Metalworks.
        I_HAVE_ORDERS_FOR_YOU_FROM_THE_PRESIDENT                                = 7422,  -- I have orders for you from the president himself. You must have heard already, but he wants you to go to Fei'Yin.
        GO_SPEAK_TO_SIR_NAJI_AT_THE_PRESIDENT                                   = 7423,  -- Go speak to Sir Naji at the President's Office. He will show you in.
        SO_IT_HAS_FINALLY_COME_TO_THIS_YOU                                      = 7424,  -- So, it has finally come to this... You are to infiltrate the Kindred's main stronghold of Zvahl.
        THE_PRESIDENT_WILL_BRIEF_YOU_HIMSELF_IN_HIS                             = 7425,  -- The president will brief you himself in his office. Good luck, adventurer!
        AH_YOU_HAVE_RETURNED_FROM_JEUNO_GO_TO                                   = 7426,  -- Ah, you have returned from Jeuno. Go to the President's Office right away. Sir Naji will show you in.
        TAKE_IT_FROM_ME_A_GUARD_S_JOB                                           = 7427,  -- Take it from me, a guard's job is pretty boring. Not that I'd rather have trouble, mind you.
        THE_NORTH_GATE_AND_BELIGEN_SQUARE_ARE_DOWN                              = 7428,  -- The North Gate and Beligen Square are down these stairs. Cross the drawbridge from the square if you want to get to the residential area.
        GO_STRAIGHT_WEST_AND_YOU_LL_COME_ACROSS                                 = 7429,  -- Go straight west and you'll come across a goods store and the tavern. Further west is the road leading to the Markets District.
        THE_RESIDENTIAL_AREA_IS_ON_THE_OTHER_SIDE                               = 7430,  -- The residential area is on the other side of this drawbridge. Cross it while it's down if you need to go to your Mog House.
        INCOMING_SHIP_EVERYONE_OFF_THE_BRIDGE                                   = 7431,  -- Incoming ship! Everyone off the bridge!
        I_M_HELPING_EVELYN_WITH_HER_STORE_SHE                                   = 7432,  -- I'm helping Evelyn with her store. She said she'd give me a present if I worked hard!
        YOU_LOST_WHERE_YOU_GOIN                                                 = 7433,  -- You lost? Where you goin'?
        WHICH_AREA_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_ASK_ABOUT                                     = 7434,  -- Which area do you want to ask about? None. The western section. The eastern section.
        ALL_RIGHTY_COME_BACK_ANYTIME_HAVE_A_NICE                                = 7435,  -- All-righty. Come back anytime. Have a nice day.
        ALL_RIGHT_LET_S_SEE_SEE_ALL_THOSE                                       = 7436,  -- All right, let's see... See all those doors to the west, there?
        THE_ONES_ON_THE_RIGHT_ARE_YOUR_RUN                                      = 7437,  -- The ones on the right are your run-of-the-mill warehouses. Some real shady characters've been seen going in there, so you be careful, all right?
        ON_THE_LEFT_YOU_VE_GOT_THE_AIR                                          = 7438,  -- On the left you've got the air travel agency, or the door to the world, as they say. You need an airship pass to get in, though. And not through that door, either--that's the exit. Heh-heh.
        THE_ENTRANCE_IS_AROUND_THE_CORNER_ONCE_YOU                              = 7439,  -- The entrance is around the corner. Once you're in, you gotta walk down to the pier to get on airships.
        AIRSHIPS_THERE_ONLY_GO_TO_JEUNO_BUT_OF                                  = 7440,  -- Airships there only go to Jeuno--but of course, you knew that, right?
        A_LITTLE_FURTHER_ON_WE_HAVE_GALVIN_S                                    = 7441,  -- A little further on, we have Galvin's Travel Gear--a goods shop. They've got a few things adventurers like yourself might need.
        ABOVE_GALVIN_S_YOU_VE_GOT_THE_STEAMING                                  = 7442,  -- Above Galvin's, you've got the Steaming Sheep Restaurant, which most people just call the tavern. It's a good place if you want to eat, drink, or hear a good story or two.
        AND_FURTHER_DOWN_WEST_YOU_LL_COME_TO                                    = 7443,  -- And further down west...you'll come to a bridge. It leads to the Markets District, a nicer part of town.
        YOU_CAN_GET_TO_BOTH_THE_METALWORKS_AND                                  = 7444,  -- You can get to both the Metalworks and the Mines District from the markets. It's like the crossroads of Bastok, if you know what I mean.
        OKAY_TO_THE_EAST_WE_VE_GOT_A                                            = 7445,  -- Okay, to the east--we've got a few houses on the left, a few merchant stalls on the right...
        OH_THOSE_MERCHANTS_DON_T_HAVE_MUCH_TO                                   = 7446,  -- Oh, those merchants don't have much to sell, by the way. They're only useful if you want to sell off stuff you don't need and go back outside right away.
        RIGHT_FURTHER_ON_DOWN_THE_STAIRS_IS_THE                                 = 7447,  -- Right, further on down the stairs is...the North Gate!
        YOU_CAN_GET_MISSIONS_FROM_THE_GUARDS_THERE                              = 7448,  -- You can get missions from the guards there or ask to join in conquests.
        JUST_SOUTH_OF_THE_SQUARE_IS_ONE_OF                                      = 7449,  -- Just south of the square is one of our major landmarks, the drawbridge!
        IT_S_GOTTA_BE_DRAWN_UP_WHEN_AIRSHIPS                                    = 7450,  -- It's gotta be drawn up when airships come in, so be careful. The residential area on the other side is where your room is. Go there if you need to store stuff.
        OH_BUT_YOU_HAVE_TO_BE_A_BASTOKER                                        = 7451,  -- Oh, but you have to be a Bastoker or have a Rent-a-Room to do that.
        THAT_S_ABOUT_IT_COME_BACK_IF_YOU                                        = 7452,  -- That's about it. Come back if you have any more questions, all right?
        THIS_BUILDING_HERE_IS_WHERE_YOU_GET_ON                                  = 7453,  -- This building here is where you get on airships. I'm usually here all day, so I hear a lot of stories about things happening in other countries.
        TRAVELING_ON_AIRSHIPS_IS_A_RIGHT_ONLY_GIVEN                             = 7454,  -- Traveling on airships is a right only given to those who've proven themselves worthy. It's still a little early for you, I would think.
        I_AM_FROM_SAN_D_ORIA_HAVE_YOU                                           = 7455,  -- I am from San d'Oria. Have you ever gone there? You do not want to. It is a nation trapped in old traditions and foolish rules.
        THE_SAN_D_ORIAN_ARMY_IS_THOUGHT_THE                                     = 7456,  -- The San d'Orian army is thought the mightiest in Vana'diel, but it is only a shadow of its past self.
        I_CHOSE_TO_LET_MY_SOUL_BE_RAVAGED                                       = 7457,  -- I chose to let my soul be ravaged by the cruel wheel of time rather than spend an eternity in that timeless city. Here, at least, I feel alive.
        RAFAELA_AND_I_LOVE_TAKING_WALKS_ALONG_THIS                              = 7458,  -- Rafaela and I love taking walks along this road. The sea wind seeps deep and soothes the soul. Do you feel it as well?
        BASTOK_S_SEA_IS_THE_SAME_SHADE_OF                                       = 7459,  -- Bastok's sea is the same shade of blue as the one near San d'Oria. They are one and the same. I do not long for my homeland anymore...I have Rafaela, now.
        SOMETIMES_AS_WE_LOOK_AT_THE_SEA_TOGETHER                                = 7460,  -- Sometimes, as we look at the sea together, Evi gets this real sad look on his face...
        AND_I_THINK_MAYBE_HE_WAS_NEVER_MEANT                                    = 7461,  -- And I think, maybe he was never meant to be one of us, and that he should not stay here in Bastok.
        ARE_YOU_LOOKING_FOR_SOMETHING_THERE_IS_NOTHING                          = 7462,  -- Are you looking for something? There is nothing here you would want.
        IF_YOU_ARE_LOOKING_FOR_MY_DAUGHTER_AYAME                                = 7463,  -- If you are looking for my daughter Ayame, she is working at the President's Office. She does not come back home often.
        EVERYONE_SAYS_THAT_THEY_RE_ALL_PROUD_OF                                 = 7464,  -- Everyone says that they're all proud of sis.
        I_AM_TOO_SHE_S_STRONG_COOL_AND                                          = 7465,  -- I am, too--she's strong, cool, and smart. I'm not any of those...I can never be like her.
        THE_HUMES_WERE_PLANNING_ON_RAISING_A_NEW                                = 7466,  -- The Humes were planning on raising a new building here.
        BUT_WHEN_THE_HUME_HEAD_ENGINEER_SWITCHED_DEPARTMENTS                    = 7467,  -- But when the Hume head engineer switched departments, they canceled the whole project, leaving us out to dry. I hate Hume bureaucracy.
        THERE_S_NOTHING_TO_SEE_HERE_JUST_ANOTHER                                = 7468,  -- There's nothing to see here. Just another forgotten Hume project, where we Galka did all the work and were left with nothing to show for our sweat and toil.
        IT_S_A_GREAT_DAY_ISN_T_IT                                               = 7469,  -- It's a great day, isn't it? Bastok has changed. There's that drawbridge there, and airships in the air... But the sun still shines as brightly as when we were children.
        THIS_USED_TO_BE_THE_SECRET_PLACE_WHERE                                  = 7470,  -- This used to be the secret place where young lovers met. Qiji and I used to come here, too, before we moved in together.
        PEOPLE_SAY_THE_DRAWBRIDGE_IS_GETTING_OLD_BUT                            = 7471,  -- People say the drawbridge is getting old, but it looks as sturdy to me as the first time I laid eyes on it. If anything has changed, it must be something within us...
        I_M_HAPPY_THAT_MY_GRANDDAUGHTER_LIKES_ME                                = 7472,  -- I'm happy that my granddaughter likes me, but I must say I have trouble keeping up with her at my age.
        C_MON_GRANDMA_OVER_HERE                                                 = 7473,  -- C'mon, Grandma! Over here!
        I_DON_T_KNOW_WHAT_S_WRONG_WITH                                          = 7474,  -- I don't know what's wrong with my son. He stays home all day and does nothing. I wish there were something I could do.
        LEAVE_ME_ALONE_I_DON_T_WANNA_GO                                         = 7475,  -- Leave me alone! I don't wanna go outside! I'm safe here...no one can hurt me...
        IT_PAYS_BETTER_TO_WORK_FOR_THE_HUMES                                    = 7476,  -- It pays better to work for the Humes in this district than to dig in the mines.
        THOSE_GOOD_FOR_NOTHING_HARD_HEADS_IN_THE                                = 7477,  -- Those good-for-nothing hard-heads in the Mines District don't know what they're missing.
        CAN_I_HELP_YOU_NO_YOU_CAN_T                                             = 7478,  -- Can I help you? No, you can't store personal items here. Our space is rented out to major trading companies and ministries of the government.
        I_VE_SEEN_SOME_REAL_SHADY_CHARACTERS_GOING                              = 7479,  -- I've seen some real shady characters going into the warehouse next door. I wonder what kind of business they're in? Actually, never mind. I don't want to know.
        WE_CAME_ALL_THE_WAY_HERE_FROM_WINDURST                                  = 7480,  -- We came all the way here from Windurst hoping to make some quick gil, but business has been rrreally slow...almost as slow as Panana's Cures.
        I_REALLY_DON_T_LIKE_FIGHTING_BUT_KONTY                                  = 7481,  -- I really don't like fighting, but Konty here takes us to dangerous places all the time!
        WHY_DID_I_EVER_AGREE_TO_LEAVE_WINDURST                                  = 7482,  -- Why did I ever agree to leave Windurst? I wanna go home... <Sigh>
        HEY_YOU_A_ROOKIE_IF_I_WERE_YOU                                          = 7483,  -- Hey, you a rookie? If I were you, I'd go hunt lizards. They're worth the trouble--take my word for it.
        CROSS_THIS_BRIDGE_TO_GO_TO_THE_MARKETS                                  = 7484,  -- Cross this bridge to go to the Markets District. Also take this road to get to the Metalworks--which include forges and administrative buildings--and the Mines District.
        AN_ELVAAN_KNIGHT_NAMED_DOMIEN                                           = 7485,  -- An Elvaan knight named Domien?
        YES_I_BELIEVE_I_VE_SEEN_SOMEONE_MATCHING                                = 7486,  -- Yes, I believe I've seen someone matching that description walk by earlier...wait, is that him?
        THAT_ARE_YOU_POWHATAN                                                   = 7487,  -- That %...are you Powhatan?
        YOU_RE_HIS_REPRESENTATIVE_NO_MATTER_YOU_SHOULD                          = 7488,  -- You're his representative? No matter--you should know that being late to a meeting is rude, not to say unforgivable, where I am from.
        I_HAVE_WRITTEN_A_LETTER_OF_COMPLAINT_TO                                 = 7489,  -- I have written a letter of complaint to Mister Powhatan. Give it to him--I am going back to Jeuno. Goodbye.
        WHAT_S_WRONG_WITH_ME_I_M_TOO                                            = 7490,  -- What's wrong with me? I'm too scared to go outside...I want to hide in a small, narrow place...
        I_NEED_SOMETHING_BIG_ENOUGH_TO_HIDE_MY                                  = 7491,  -- I need something big enough to hide my whole body! Do you have something like that? Can you find one for me? Please?
        YES_YES_THIS_IS_GREAT_FINALLY_I_CAN                                     = 7492,  -- Yes, yes! This is great! Finally, I can sleep in peace! I'm never going out again! Hah hah!
        AH_IT_S_YOU_THAT_SHELL_YOU_GAVE                                         = 7493,  -- Ah, it's you! That shell you gave me is great! I must've been a turtle in a past life!
        YOU_YOU_RE_THE_ONE_WHO_GAVE_MY                                          = 7494,  -- You! You're the one who gave my son that cursed thing, aren't you!?
        THANKS_TO_YOU_NOT_ONLY_DOES_HE_NEVER                                    = 7495,  -- Thanks to you, not only does he never go out, he stays in that shell all day!
        DO_SOMETHING_ISN_T_THERE_ANYTHING_YOU_CAN                               = 7496,  -- Do something! Isn't there anything you can do to make him come out of his shell?
        IT_S_YOUR_FAULT_PANANA_I_KNEW_I                                         = 7497,  -- It's your fault, Panana! I knew I shouldn't have let you talk me into going to Beadeaux! Now I've got these itchy bugs all over me!
        THAT_S_NOT_MY_FAULT_I_DID_WARN                                          = 7498,  -- That's not my fault! I did warn you about looking for treasure-pleasure inside Quadav shells!
        EVERYONE_KNOWS_THEY_RE_FULL_OF_YOU_HAVE                                 = 7499,  -- Everyone knows they're full of %! You have to be careful when you touch them!
        DON_T_YOU_KNOW_THE_SAYING_PUTTING_IN                                    = 7500,  -- Don't you know the saying, putting % in a Quadav shell? It means, stirring up trouble!
        WHAT_IS_THIS_AH_OF_COURSE_PUTTING_IN                                    = 7501,  -- What is this? Ah, of course! Putting % in a Quadav shell! All I have to do is put this nasty little thing in my son's shell, right?
        I_LL_GO_DO_IT_RIGHT_AWAY_COME                                           = 7502,  -- I'll go do it right away! Come back later--I'll give you a reward if it works!
        MY_SHELL_BECAME_REALLY_ITCHY_ALL_OF_A                                   = 7503,  -- My shell became really itchy all of a sudden...
        NOW_I_WONDER_WHY_I_WANTED_TO_HIDE                                       = 7504,  -- Now I wonder why I wanted to hide in that thing in the first place...
        OH_THERE_YOU_ARE_THAT_TRICK_OF_YOURS                                    = 7505,  -- Oh, there you are! That trick of yours worked! Now, if only my son would go out... Anyway, here's something for your trouble.
        I_M_TELLING_YOU_IT_S_THOSE_QUADAV                                       = 7506,  -- I'm telling you, it's those Quadav. They must've put some kind of curse on him!
        MY_NEIGHBOR_ENSETSU_S_DAUGHTER_AYAME_IS_QUITE                           = 7507,  -- My neighbor Ensetsu's daughter, Ayame, is quite a remarkable girl. Have you met her yet?
        SHE_S_ALWAYS_BEEN_VERY_BRIGHT_SHE_BECAME                                = 7508,  -- She's always been very bright. She became a samurai when she was little, and now she made it to the top and became a Mythril Musketeer!
        ONLY_THE_TOP_FIVE_MUSKETEERS_CAN_JOIN_THEIR                             = 7509,  -- Only the top five Musketeers can join their ranks, you know. Ensetsu must be proud that Ayame was chosen to be one!
        NOW_IF_ONLY_HER_SISTER_KAEDE_WERE_A                                     = 7510,  -- Now, if only her sister Kaede were a little more like her. She's so quiet and unremarkable...but I suppose children should be seen and not heard.
        I_NEVER_SEE_MUCH_OF_CORANN_OH_THAT                                      = 7511,  -- I never see much of Corann... Oh, that's the son of my neighbor Ronan. I think he stays cooped up in his room all day.
        HE_S_LIKE_A_TURTLE_IN_ITS_SHELL                                         = 7512,  -- He's like a turtle in its shell... So much so that some people even say that the turtle people cast a curse on him when he was born!
        THE_TAVERN_S_UP_THESE_STEPS_THE_GOODS                                   = 7513,  -- The tavern's up these steps. The goods shop and the bridge leading to the Markets District is straight to the west.
        TO_THE_EAST_IS_THE_NORTH_GATE_AND                                       = 7514,  -- To the east is the North Gate and the drawbridge leading to the residential area. That's about it.
        I_STARTED_WORKING_FOR_THE_AIR_TRAVEL_AGENCY                             = 7515,  -- I started working for the air travel agency hoping to become an airship pilot someday, but all they make me do is move boxes and crates.
        MAYBE_I_SHOULD_VE_GONE_TO_JEUNO_INSTEAD                                 = 7516,  -- Maybe I should've gone to Jeuno instead. Jeuno is where all the airships go, you know? Like that saying, All routes lead to Jeuno, or something like that.
        DUE_TO_TECHNICAL_DIFFICULTIES_WE_CANNOT_ISSUE_WORLD                     = 7517,  -- Due to technical difficulties, we cannot issue World Passes at this time.
        THIS_IS_WHERE_WE_ISSUE_WORLD_PASSES_A                                   = 7518,  -- This is where we issue World Passes. A World Pass allows you to invite people from other worlds to join you.
        YOUR_WORLD_PASS_IS                                                      = 7519,  -- Your World Pass is: %.
        BE_WARNED_THAT_YOU_CAN_ONLY_INVITE_A                                    = 7520,  -- Be warned that you can only invite a limited number of people to this world with your World Pass.
        THIS_IS_SUCH_A_GREAT_LOCATION_I_WISH                                    = 7521,  -- This is such a great location... I wish the Humes hadn't dropped the whole project.
        YOU_SHOULD_VE_SEEN_US_WHEN_THE_FOREMAN                                  = 7522,  -- You should've seen us when the foreman was still here! We were busy like bees, but happy as lambs to take part in this big project. But look at us now.
        THE_FOREMAN_TOOK_IT_THE_HARDEST_HE_DISAPPEARED                          = 7523,  -- The foreman took it the hardest. He disappeared when the project was canceled. I think his dog went with him, too.
        I_WONDER_WHAT_HAPPENED_TO_HIM_IT_S                                      = 7524,  -- I wonder what happened to him? It's still a little too early for him to have left on his journey of rebirth...
        SAY_YOU_RE_AN_ADVENTURER_AREN_T_YOU                                     = 7525,  -- Say, you're an adventurer, aren't you? Can you tell me if you hear anything about our foreman or his dog?
        THE_FOREMAN_TOLD_ME_NOT_TO_TELL_ANYONE                                  = 7526,  -- The foreman told me not to tell anyone, but he said he was going to the big hill in North Gustaberg.
        HE_TOLD_ME_THAT_HE_D_BE_GONE                                            = 7527,  -- He told me that he'd be gone for a while, so he asked me to take care of his dog for him while he was away.
        BUT_THE_DAY_AFTER_THE_FOREMAN_LEFT_HIS                                  = 7528,  -- But the day after the foreman left, his dog disappeared, too. I hope they're both all right...
        HEY_THE_FOREMAN_S_DOG_USED_TO_WEAR                                      = 7529,  -- Hey...the foreman's dog used to wear this collar. What would an undead cur--in North Gustaberg, of all places--be doing with it?
        SOME_SAY_THAT_WHEN_YOU_DIE_THE_REGRET                                   = 7530,  -- Some say that when you die, the regret you have about things you left undone could turn you into an undead, but...is this possible?
        IF_THAT_WAS_THE_FOREMAN_S_DOG_YOU                                       = 7531,  -- If that was the foreman's dog you fought, then that would mean the foreman is also...
        NO_HE_CANNOT_BE_HE_MUST_HAVE_ALREADY                                    = 7532,  -- No, he cannot be. He must have already reincarnated into a new body. He used to say that this project might be his last job...
        I_JUST_WISH_WE_COULD_VE_FINISHED_IT                                     = 7533,  -- I just wish we could've finished it, for the foreman's sake.
        IN_ANY_CASE_I_SHOULD_THANK_YOU_FOR                                      = 7534,  -- In any case, I should thank you for this bit of news, be it good or ill. Here, take this. It isn't much, but it should come in handy.
        THE_STAMP_HUNT_RIGHT_YES_YOU_RE_NOT                                     = 7535,  -- The stamp hunt, right? Yes, you're not the first adventurer who has come to me asking for it. Here you go.
        YOU_RECEIVED_A_STAMP                                                    = 7536,  -- You received a stamp!
        HUNTING_WHAT_OH_STAMPS_RIGHT_I_M_SUPPOSED                               = 7537,  -- Hunting what? Oh, stamps. Right, I'm supposed to give those out, too. Here.
        I_DON_T_KNOW_WHAT_I_M_SUPPOSED                                          = 7538,  -- I don't know what I'm supposed to be looking out for here. Sure, there are those griping Galka at the construction site and shady dealings in the warehouses, but those are nothing new.
        I_NEED_A_FAVOR_I_WANT_TO_GIVE                                           = 7539,  -- I need a favor. I want to give my wife Romilda here a present.
        SHOULD_DO_NICELY_COULD_YOU_GO_GET_ME                                    = 7540,  -- % should do nicely...could you go get me one?
        OH_THE_BUT_I_M_A_LITTLE_TOO                                             = 7541,  -- Oh! The %! But I'm a little too embarrassed to give it to her myself...could you do it for me?
        MY_FOR_ME_WHY_THAT_S_VERY_NICE                                          = 7542,  -- My! %, for me? Why, that's very nice of you!
        QIJI_LOOK_AT_WHAT_THIS_NICE_PERSON_GAVE                                 = 7543,  -- Qiji, look at what this nice person gave me! And you haven't given me a present in ages! Shame on you!
        B_BUT_THAT_S                                                            = 7544,  -- B-but, that's--
        THANK_YOU_VERY_MUCH_I_VE_WANTED_ONE                                     = 7545,  -- Thank you very much! I've wanted one of these for the longest time. It's as if you read my mind!
        UH                                                                      = 7546,  -- Uh...
        WELL_AS_LONG_AS_SHE_S_HAPPY_I                                           = 7547,  -- Well, as long as she's happy, I can't complain. Here's something for your trouble.
        YES_OF_COURSE_I_KNOW_THAT_PRESENT_WAS                                   = 7548,  -- Yes? Of course I know that present was from my husband, dear. He thinks I'm hard of hearing, but he's the one who can't even hear himself talk!
        IN_FACT_THIS_ISN_T_THE_FIRST_TIME                                       = 7549,  -- In fact, this isn't the first time he's done this. But you know what? It's a wonderful thing to receive a gift from someone who loves you, no matter how many times, or how old you are.
        I_SHOULD_GIVE_QIJI_SOMETHING_BACK_FOR_HIS                               = 7550,  -- I should give Qiji something back for his present this time, too. Would you be kind enough to go find me %, dear?
        OH_AND_DON_T_WORRY_I_CAN_GIVE                                           = 7551,  -- Oh, and don't worry, I can give them to him myself. Men are such cowards!
        AH_YOU_VE_BROUGHT_THEM_THANK_YOU_HERE                                   = 7552,  -- Ah, you've brought them. Thank you. Here's something for you.
        HMM_YOU_WHAT_ARE_YOU_GIVING_HER_IS                                      = 7553,  -- Hmm? You! What are you giving her? Is that some present from another man!?
        OH_DON_T_BE_FOOLISH_QIJI_THIS_NICE                                      = 7554,  -- Oh, don't be foolish, Qiji. This nice person just brought me what I asked for--a present from me to you. Here.
        PRESENT_OH_OF_COURSE_YOU_WOULD_YOU_NEVER                                = 7555,  -- Present? Oh! %! Of course you would! You never could resist my charms! <Wink, wink> Heh-heh.
        YES_YES_AH_HERE_TAKE_THIS_THANK_YOU                                     = 7556,  -- Yes, yes... Ah, here, take this. Thank you again.
        OH_AND_ONE_MORE_THING_SEEING_OR_HEARING                                 = 7557,  -- Oh, and...one more thing. Seeing or hearing things the same way isn't important. Sharing the same moments in your life is.
        QIJI_TOLD_ME_THAT_WHEN_HE_PROPOSED_TO                                   = 7558,  -- Qiji told me that when he proposed to me. I'd like to think that's why we're still together.
        I_MUST_ASK_YOU_TO_DO_SOMETHING_FOR                                      = 7559,  -- I must ask you to do something for me. You see, I was once a knight of San d'Oria. I left the Order and came here, to Bastok, when I realized the futility of their ways.
        ON_MY_WAY_HERE_I_BURIED_MY_MISSION                                      = 7560,  -- On my way here, I buried my mission orders for that day near the windmills in Konschtat. It was a dishonorable thing to do, and I regret doing it now...
        EVI_YOU_RE_NOT_GOING_BACK_ARE_YOU                                       = 7561,  -- Evi? You're not going back, are you?
        DO_NOT_WORRY_RAFAELA_I_AM_NOT_THAT                                      = 7562,  -- Do not worry, Rafaela, I am not. That paper is a testament to my past failures... I just wish to rip it apart with my own hands, and finally start anew.
        IF_YOU_HAPPEN_TO_GO_TO_THE_KONSCHTAT                                    = 7563,  -- If you happen to go to the Konschtat Highlands, would you try retrieving it for me? Unfortunately, I cannot remember which windmill I buried it near...
        YES_THIS_IS_IT_FINALLY_I_MAY_START                                      = 7564,  -- Yes, this is it. Finally, I may start anew. Take this as a token of my gratitude. I do not need it anymore.
        AH_I_WISH_I_HAD_TIME_TO_CHAT                                            = 7565,  -- Ah, I wish I had time to chat, but I'm a little busy at the moment.
        I_AM_THE_OWNER_OF_THIS_ESTABLISHMENT_BUT                                = 7566,  -- I am the owner of this establishment, but I have yet to get used to doing all these chores...
        YES_IF_THERE_S_ANYTHING_YOU_CAN_DO                                      = 7567,  -- Yes? If there's anything you can do to help? Well, we're running a little low on salt, and I'm having trouble with the bookkeeping, and...
        OH_IT_S_NO_USE_I_VE_BEEN                                                = 7568,  -- Oh, it's no use. I've been trying to manage this restaurant ever since my husband died twenty years ago, but I still can't do anything properly...
        THE_OTHER_DAY_A_CUSTOMER_ORDERED_BUT_I                                  = 7569,  -- The other day, a customer ordered %, but I haven't been able to get any.
        HE_WAS_A_REGULAR_CUSTOMER_WHEN_MY_HUSBAND                               = 7570,  -- He was a regular customer when my husband ran this place, so I wish I could serve him the next time he comes in.
        ISN_T_THIS_YES_IT_IS_THANK_YOU                                          = 7571,  -- Isn't this...? Yes, it is %! Thank you so much! Oh! I should pay you for your trouble...
        YOU_WERE_ASKED_TO_HELP_ME_BUT_WHO                                       = 7572,  -- You were asked to help me? But who would...? The Chief Engineer himself?
        I_SEE_LET_US_GO_UPSTAIRS_THERE_ARE                                      = 7573,  -- I see... Let us go upstairs--there are a few things I should tell you.
        CHIEF_CID_WAS_A_CLOSE_FRIEND_OF_MY                                      = 7574,  -- Chief Cid was a close friend of my husband's. He was the one who gave my husband his job in the Palborough Mines. Digging mythril there earned him enough gil to open this restaurant.
        THEN_TWENTY_YEARS_AGO_THEY_DISCOVERED_A_NEW                             = 7575,  -- Then, twenty years ago, they discovered a new vein of mythril in the Palborough Mines, and my husband, though long retired by then, was called in to oversee the diggings.
        THINGS_WERE_GOING_SMOOTHLY_UNTIL_A_BATCH_OF                             = 7576,  -- Things were going smoothly until...a batch of the new type of explosives they were using went off without warning, and as if waiting for such an opportunity, the Quadav attacked.
        YOU_MUST_HAVE_GUESSED_BY_NOW_CHIEF_ENGINEER                             = 7577,  -- You must have guessed by now--Chief Engineer Cid was the one who designed the formula for the new explosive.
        I_WOULD_BE_LYING_IF_I_SAID_I                                            = 7578,  -- I would be lying if I said I never blamed Cid for my husband's death...even though my husband would surely have forgiven him.
        GIVE_THIS_LETTER_TO_CID_FOR_ME_TELL                                     = 7579,  -- Give this letter to Cid for me. Tell him he doesn't have to worry about me, or this restaurant.
        AH_IT_S_YOU_THAT_CUSTOMER_I_TOLD                                        = 7580,  -- Ah, it's you. That customer I told you about came back, and I was able to serve him % this time, thanks to you.
        HE_SAID_HE_USED_TO_WORK_WITH_MY                                         = 7581,  -- He said he used to work with my husband in the Metalworks before he retired.
        HE_WANTED_TO_HAVE_THE_NEXT_TIME_HE                                      = 7582,  -- He wanted to have % the next time he comes, but I don't know where to get one...
        OH_MY_WHEREVER_DID_YOU_FIND_THIS_THANK                                  = 7583,  -- Oh, my! Wherever did you find this? Thank you, you've saved me again! I must tell that customer to come back...
        OH_BUT_I_FORGOT_TO_ASK_HIM_HIS                                          = 7584,  -- Oh, but I forgot to ask him his name! He said he still worked in the Metalworks...
        HE_SAID_HE_USED_TO_WORK_WITH_MY_2                                       = 7585,  -- He said he used to work with my husband there. He's a Galka, very reserved but polite. Do you know him?
        IF_YOU_DO_SEE_HIM_COULD_YOU_GIVE                                        = 7586,  -- If you do see him, could you give him this letter of invitation for me?
        DID_YOU_GIVE_MY_LETTER_TO_MY_CUSTOMER                                   = 7587,  -- Did you give my letter to my customer? You did? Thank you. You say his name is Raibaht?
        HE_WORKS_IN_CID_S_LAB_AS_THE                                            = 7588,  -- He works in Cid's lab as the Chief Engineer's aide? Now that you mention it, I do remember hearing his name before...
        OH                                                                      = 7589,  -- Oh!
        THANK_YOU_FOR_YOUR_INVITATION_MS_HILDA_I                                = 7590,  -- Thank you for your invitation, Ms. Hilda. I must apologize for my lack of manners for ordering dishes and not even leaving my name.
        PLEASE_MISTER_RAIBAHT_COME_THIS_WAY                                     = 7591,  -- Please, Mister Raibaht, come this way.
        YOUR_HUSBAND_AND_I_WERE_HIRED_THE_SAME                                  = 7592,  -- Your husband and I were hired the same year by the Metalworks Department of Mining. But we were never on good terms, to say the least.
        THEN_WHY                                                                = 7593,  -- Then why...?
        MOST_HUMES_ONLY_THINK_OF_US_AS_BIG                                      = 7594,  -- Most Humes only think of us as big brutes...but your husband was the only one to see me, a Galka, as someone worthy enough to be his rival.
        THE_OTHER_HUMES_DID_NOT_EVEN_CONSIDER_ME                                = 7595,  -- The other Humes did not even consider me capable of being a scientist. Your husband, though, would come to me every time he made a breakthrough...and brag.
        YOU_MAY_LAUGH_BUT_I_CANNOT_EXPLAIN_HOW                                  = 7596,  -- You may laugh, but I cannot explain how happy I was that he would come to me, and no one else.
        YES_MY_HUSBAND_WAS_LIKE_THAT_HE_WAS                                     = 7597,  -- Yes, my husband was like that. He was outspoken, honest about his feelings, even childish in some ways. His wanting to open this restaurant, for example...
        YES_I_WAS_DISMAYED_AT_FIRST_WHEN_HE                                     = 7598,  -- Yes. I was dismayed at first when he decided to retire, but after seeing this place...I understand why.
        WHEN_DID_YOU_DECIDE_TO_WORK_FOR_THE                                     = 7599,  -- When did you decide to work for the Chief Engineer? I didn't think his kind of work was in your field of expertise.
        YOUR_HUSBAND_USED_TO_TELL_ME_ABOUT_HIM                                  = 7600,  -- Your husband used to tell me about him. When I learned that it was his invention that caused your husband's demise, I decided to approach him, without revealing my true intents.
        WHAT_WERE_YOU_THINKING_OF_DOING                                         = 7601,  -- What were you thinking of doing!?
        I_WANTED_TO_SEE_WHAT_KIND_OF_MAN                                        = 7602,  -- I wanted to see what kind of man could live with the death of so many on his conscience...but I have yet to understand him fully. He is more complex than any equation I've had to solve.
        BUT_DO_NOT_WORRY_MADAM_VENGEANCE_IS_LONG                                = 7603,  -- But do not worry, madam--vengeance is long gone from my mind. I understand now why your husband was so fond of him. He and Cid are very much alike.
        YES_I_KNOW                                                              = 7604,  -- Yes...I know.
        I_WILL_STUDY_CID_S_WORK_AND_WHEN                                        = 7605,  -- I will study Cid's work, and when I understand it fully, I will pass that knowledge down to future generations.
        THAT_IS_WHAT_YOUR_HUSBAND_WOULD_HAVE_WANTED                             = 7606,  -- That is what your husband would have wanted me to do. I know that now.
