        YES_I_AM_THE_ONE_WHO_WROTE_IT                                           = 7652,  -- %... Yes, I am the one who wrote it. I have also been sending the birds, hoping she might get it.
        I_MET_HER_ON_THE_SHORES_OF_THE                                          = 7653,  -- I met her on the shores of the Gustaberg river. She was an adventurer, as I was in those days. She was...as beautiful as a siren.
        WE_PROMISED_EACH_OTHER_WE_WOULD_TRAVEL_TO                               = 7654,  -- We promised each other we would travel to the Northlands together someday. When we went, we would board the ship that flies toward the stars of Ifrit...
        BUT_IN_ORDER_TO_DO_THAT_I_NEEDED                                        = 7655,  -- But in order to do that, I needed money. So I sold the % that had brought us together.
        BY_LETTING_IT_GO_OUR_BOND_WAS_WEAKENED                                  = 7656,  -- By letting it go, our bond was weakened. We started to slowly drift apart...and one day, she was gone.
        I_WAS_HOPING_THAT_SHE_WOULD_BOARD_THAT                                  = 7657,  -- I was hoping that she would board that airship to go to the Northlands someday, and find my letter waiting for her. It was a long shot, but I had to try.
        I_HAD_WRITTEN_A_SONG_ABOUT_THE_NORTHLANDS                               = 7658,  -- I had written a song about the Northlands as well, but...this has gone on long enough. It is time to end it.
