        HMPH_IT_SEEMS_YOU                                                       = 13352,  -- Hmph. It seems you [are hardly fit to be disemboweled by these fiends, so superior are they to you/can hold your own against these colossi of combat/have transcended even these ferocities and reign over all with an iron fist].
        WHY_HELLO_THERE_MY_TREMENDOUS_TASK_IS_TO                                = 13354,  -- Why, hello there! My tremendous task is to tabulate your precious points for the login campaign and exchange them for pleasing prizes, kupo!
        WHY_HELLO_THERE_MY_TREMENDOUS_TASK_IS_TO_2                              = 13355,  -- Why, hello there! My tremendous task is to tabulate your precious points for the [/January/February/March/April/May/June/July/August/September/October/November/December] # login campaign and exchange them for pleasing prizes, kupo!
        WHAT_CAN_I_ASSIST_YOU_WITH_PT_CHECK                                     = 13356,  -- What can I assist you with? (# pt[/s].) Check/Exchange points. Learn about the campaign. Nothing.
        IN_THIS_LOGIN_CAMPAIGN_WE_PROVIDE_YOU_WITH                              = 13357,  -- In this login campaign, we provide you with points just for logging in once each day (Earth time), kupo!
        YOU_CAN_TRADE_THEM_FOR_INCREDIBLE_ITEMS_TO                              = 13358,  -- You can trade them for incredible items to assist you with your adventures!
        YOU_CAN_EVEN_PROCURE_MORE_POINTS_BY_LOGGING                             = 13359,  -- You can even procure more points by logging in routinely, which we all want, since Vana'diel always anxiously awaits your appearance!
        YOU_CAN_TRADE_IN_THESE_TOKENS_FOR_OUR                                   = 13360,  -- You can trade in these tokens for our gratuitous gifts any time during this campaign!
        EVEN_WHEN_THE_POINT_PROFFERING_PERIOD_HAS_PASSED                        = 13361,  -- Even when the point-proffering period has passed, you can still acquire these amazing items for a limited time, so don't forget about me, kupo!
        UP_TO_700_POINTS_FROM_THE_CURRENT_CAMPAIGN                              = 13362,  -- Up to 700 points from the current campaign can be carried over to the next one starting with the October 2025 login campaign!
        ANY_ADDITIONAL_POINTS_WILL_BE_SUMMARILY_SEIZED_KUPO                     = 13363,  -- Any additional points will be summarily seized, kupo!
        VIEW_WHICH_ITEM_PTS_POINT_ITEMS_PT_ITEMS                                = 13364,  -- View which item? (# pts.) #-point items. #-pt. items. #-pt. items. #-pt. items. #-pt. items. #-pt. items. #-pt. items. #-pt. items. Back.
        PT_ITEMS_PTS_BACK                                                       = 13365,  -- #-pt. items (# pts.): %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. Back.
        COSTS_POINT                                                             = 13366,  -- % costs # point[/s]. [You don't have enough points, kupo./Purchase this prize, kupo?/]
        HOW_MANY_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_KUPO                                            = 13367,  -- How many would you like, kupo?
        ALTANA_ABOVE_YOU_DO_NOT_POSSESS_THE_PREREQUISITE                        = 13368,  -- Altana above! You do not possess the prerequisite number of points!
        PROCEED_WITH_EXCHANGE_PT_YES_NO                                         = 13369,  -- Proceed with exchange? (# pt[/s].) Yes. No.
        WAIT_ONE_SHORT_SECOND_WHILE_I_GET_YOUR                                  = 13370,  -- Wait one short second while I get your goods!
        SOMETHING_WENT_WRONG_KUPO_TRY_AGAIN_LATER                               = 13371,  -- Something went wrong, kupo! Try again later.
        HEY_YOU_ABLE_ADVENTURER_CAST_YOUR_GAZE_ON                               = 13372,  -- Hey, you--able adventurer! Cast your gaze on the countenance of this misbegotten mutant.
        GLANCE_AT_THE_GOOD_NATURED_GLIMMER_IN_HIS                               = 13373,  -- Glance at the good-natured glimmer in his eyes!
        TAKE_IN_HIS_TINY_TEETH_SCINTILLATING_IN_THE                             = 13374,  -- Take in his tiny teeth scintillating in the sunlight, kupo!
        YOU_MEAN_YOU_RE_FAMILIAR_WITH_ITS_FURRY                                 = 13375,  -- You mean...you're familiar with its furry form?
        OH_HUSH_HUSTLER_LISTEN_TO_THE_LOWDOWN_BEFORE                            = 13376,  -- Oh hush, hustler. Listen to the lowdown before you loosen your lips.
        REMEMBER_THE_GRISTLY_GREEN_GOBS_WHO_CAME_BEFORE                         = 13377,  -- Remember the gristly green gobs who came before? Now its mauve and maroon mates have come to wreak wrongdoings upon our realm!
        AT_LEAST_I_SUPPOSE_SO_THEY_HAVEN_T                                      = 13378,  -- At least, I suppose so. They haven't lifted a limb of late, so maybe there should be nothing nagging at my noggin after all...
        LET_ME_TELL_YOU_A_TROUBLED_TALE_NOT                                     = 13379,  -- Let me tell you a troubled tale. Not long ago, some grisly green gobs came to Vana'diel, and we amassed a fabulous fortune crafting countless curios in their likeness.
        BUT_THERE_WAS_AN_INCONSEQUENTIAL_ISSUE_WITH_THEM                        = 13380,  -- But there was an--inconsequential?--issue with them consuming crystals like crunchy candies.
        THANKS_TO_HARDY_HEROES_AND_MOOGLE_MAGIC_WE                              = 13381,  -- Thanks to hardy heroes and moogle magic, we turned them into cerulean stone shards and sent them scurrying home, kupo.
        BUT_WE_GAVE_THE_VICTORS_GREAT_GIFTS_RESEMBLING                          = 13382,  -- But we gave the victors great gifts resembling those rowdy ruffians, so our profits plummeted and we had to cancel our tropical travel plans...
        BUT_THE_PAST_IS_IN_THE_PAST_WE                                          = 13383,  -- But the past is in the past. We must make the most of the moment!
        AND_SO_WITH_THE_MULTICOLORED_MONSTERS_NOW_MANIFESTING                   = 13384,  -- And so! With the multicolored monsters now manifesting themselves, we found our next best chance!
        THEY_HAVEN_T_LIFTED_A_LIMB_OF_LATE                                      = 13385,  -- They haven't lifted a limb of late, so maybe there's nothing to knock my noggin over...
        THUS_WE_HAVE_AN_OSTENSIBLY_OUTSTANDING_OPPORTUNITY_TO                   = 13386,  -- Thus, we have an ostensibly outstanding opportunity to manufacture new knickknacks, kupo!
        PART_OF_THE_PROCEEDS_WILL_BE_DIVERTED_TO                                = 13387,  -- Part of the proceeds will be diverted to do up dilapidated Mog Houses, with the rest funding our jovial jaunts!
        KUPOPOPO_HOW_MAGNIFICENTLY_MARVELOUS                                    = 13388,  -- Kupopopo! How magnificently marvelous!
        YOU_CAN_T_DISCERN_THE_DIFFERENCE_BETWEEN_THE                            = 13389,  -- You can't discern the difference between the dimensional delegates?
        GIVE_THEM_A_GOOD_GLANCE                                                 = 13390,  -- Give them a good glance!
        I_GUESS_THEIR_TERRIBLE_TEETH_AND_ENCHANTING_EYES                        = 13391,  -- I guess their terrible teeth and enchanting eyes do look alike...
        BUT_THE_METAL_IN_THEIR_MITTS_AND_TRINKETS                               = 13392,  -- But the metal in their mitts and trinkets on their waists! Those are different, kupo!
        WONDERFUL_WE_CAN_CUT_DOWN_ON_COSTS_AND                                  = 13393,  -- Wonderful! We can cut down on costs and rake in the revenue! Vivacious vacations for all!
        A_AH_FORGET_MY_FRIVOLOUS_FETTERING                                      = 13394,  -- A-ah! Forget my frivolous fettering.
        BUT_IF_WE_CAPTURED_THE_CERULEAN_CREATURES_BEFORE                        = 13395,  -- But if we captured the cerulean creatures before, then how did they surreptitiously scuttle back?
        UNDENIABLY_UNIMPORTANT_WHAT_MATTERS_MOST_IS_THE_MOMENT                  = 13396,  -- Undeniably unimportant. What matters most is the moment!
        OH_HO_A_COVERT_COMMUNIQUE_FROM_MY_COHORT                                = 13397,  -- Oh ho? A covert communique from my cohort in charge of the stone shard storage.
        YES_MM_HMM_MM_HMM                                                       = 13398,  -- Yes? Mm hmm... Mm hmm...
        ALTANA_KUPO_IT_ALL                                                      = 13399,  -- Altana kupo it all!
        THE_ONES_WE_PREVIOUSLY_PETRIFIED_HAVE_ESCAPED_AND                       = 13400,  -- The ones we previously petrified have escaped, and they're traipsing outside town!
        THEN_AGAIN_THE_CLOCK_WAS_TICKING_ON_THE                                 = 13401,  -- Then again, the clock was ticking on the enchantment expiring.
        AND_NOW_A_NUANCED_NOTIFICATION_FROM_OUTSIDE_TOWN                        = 13402,  -- ...And now a nuanced notification from outside town? Oh, dear.
        TH_THEN_IT_S_TRUE_KUPO                                                  = 13403,  -- Th-then it's true, kupo!
        GREAT_GASPING_GOBLINS_THOSE_FURRY_FREAKS_ARE_CAPTURING                  = 13404,  -- Great gasping Goblins! Those furry freaks are capturing crystals again!
        AND_THEIR_BESPECKLED_BRETHREN_ARE_HELPING_KUPO                          = 13405,  -- And their bespeckled brethren are helping, kupo!
        IF_THEY_SUCCEED_IN_PILFERING_OUR_PRECIOUS_PRIZES                        = 13406,  -- If they succeed in pilfering our precious prizes, Vana'diel will descend into a desolate decay!
        AND_WORSE_SNAFU_WILL_SURELY_STAIN_THE_M                                 = 13407,  -- And worse, snafu will surely stain the M.H.M.U.'s resplendent reputation!
        MOST_EXCELLENT_EXPLORER_PLEASE_TRAVEL_OUTSIDE_TOWN_AND                  = 13408,  -- Most excellent explorer, please travel outside town and round up these recidivist reprobates!
        A_MIXTURE_OF_MOOGLE_MAGIC_WILL_ENABLE_YOU                               = 13409,  -- A mixture of moogle magic will enable you to ensconce the evildoers by subjugating them into stone shards.
        OF_COURSE_I_LL_REWARD_YOUR_RIGHTEOUSNESS_WITH                           = 13410,  -- Of course, I'll reward your righteousness with the requisite remuneration, kupo.
        BUT_SINCE_WE_HAVE_SUCH_A_SHORT_SUPPLY                                   = 13411,  -- But since we have such a short supply of stuff, I have to let Lady Luck look upon you with...a lottery!
        THE_MOST_PRESTIGIOUS_PRIZES_ARE_AWARDED_IN_THE                          = 13412,  -- The most prestigious prizes are awarded in the order of mauve, vermilion, and chartruese stone shards.
        THE_GOODS_WE_VE_GATHERED_CAN_BE_CHOSEN                                  = 13413,  -- The goods we've gathered can be chosen from a long list that lengthens depending on your success.
        SIMPLY_STATED_IF_YOU_PROCURE_FIRST_PRIZE_YOU                            = 13414,  -- Simply stated, if you procure first prize, you can select spoils from lower levels should you deign to do so. And so on.
        THIS_IS_A_DIRE_DILEMMA_SO_I_SHALL                                       = 13415,  -- This is a dire dilemma, so I shall send you off to the outskirts immediately. Are you ready, kupo?
        BE_TELEPORTED_OUTSIDE_OF_TOWN_YOU_BET_I                                 = 13416,  -- Be teleported outside of town? You bet! I don't think so.
        READY_AND_RARING_TO_GO_THE_M_H                                          = 13417,  -- Ready and raring to go! The M.H.M.U.--and all Vana'diel--appreciates your assistance!
        O_OH_DEAR_KUPO_BUT_WE_REALLY_REQUIRE                                    = 13418,  -- O-oh dear, kupo... But we really require reinforcements! Please reconsider, kupo!
        YOU_HAVE_PHENOMENALLY_PROCURED_A_PRODIGIOUS_AMOUNT_OF                   = 13419,  -- You have phenomenally procured a prodigious amount of # chartruese stone shard[/s], # vermilion stone shard[/s], and # mauve stone shard[/s]. What would you like, kupo?
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_SPIN_THE_WHEEL_CHARTRUESE                              = 13420,  -- What will you do? Spin the wheel! (# chartruese shard[/s]) Spin the wheel! (# vermilion shard[/s]) Spin the wheel! (# mauve shard[/s]) Check the item list. Warp outside town. Nothing.
        YOU_HAVE_NOT_HARVESTED_A_SUFFICIENT_SUPPLY_OF                           = 13421,  -- You have not harvested a sufficient supply of [mauve stone shards/vermilion stone shards/chartruese stone shards], kupo! Clobber more critters and come back later!
        ALTANA_ABOVE_KUPO                                                       = 13422,  -- Altana above, kupo!
        CONGRATULATIONS                                                         = 13423,  -- Congratulations!
        YOU_RE_MORE_LIKELY_TO_GET_ON_A                                          = 13424,  -- You're more likely to get on a hot streak thanks to the intricacies of that item!
        YOU_ARE_ON_A_HOT_STREAK                                                 = 13425,  -- You are on a hot streak!
        YOUR_HOT_STREAK_HAS_BURNED_OUT                                          = 13426,  -- Your hot streak has burned out.
        ROLL_THEM_BONES_KUPO                                                    = 13427,  -- Roll them bones, kupo!
        AND_THE_OUTSTANDING_OUTCOME_IS                                          = 13428,  -- And the outstanding outcome is...
        ID_13429                                                                = 13429,  -- [.../First prize! Absolutely amazing!/Second prize! Emphatically excellent!/Third prize! Positively peachy!]
        THE_BOOBY_PRIZE_KUPO                                                    = 13430,  -- ...the booby prize, kupo...
        SELECT_YOUR_PRIZE_FROM_THE_LONG_LIST_I                                  = 13431,  -- Select your prize from the long list I'm about to lay upon you, kupo!
        ID_13432                                                                = 13432,  -- [What would you like/View which item]? %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. [I'll decide later/I'm done].
        WOULD_YOU_LIKE_THIS_ITEM_KUPO                                           = 13433,  -- Would you like this item, kupo?
        REALLY_SELECT_THAT_ITEM_UNDOUBTEDLY_LET_ME_THINK                        = 13434,  -- Really select that item? Undoubtedly. Let me think on it.
        COME_BACK_AND_CALL_UPON_ME_WHEN_YOU                                     = 13435,  -- Come back and call upon me when you determine which doodad you desire!
        VIEW_WHICH_CATEGORY_FIRST_PRIZE_SECOND_PRIZE_THIRD                      = 13436,  -- View which category? First prize. Second prize. Third prize. Booby prize. None for now.
        IT_GOES_SOMETHING_LIKE_THIS_KUPO                                        = 13437,  -- It goes something like this, kupo.
        THAT_LITTLE_BLACK_BUGGER_HAS_BEEN_STARING_INTO                          = 13438,  -- That little black bugger has been staring into your soul for some time now, kupo.
        DON_T_BE_CHARMED_BY_ITS_CONNIVING_COUNTENANCE                           = 13439,  -- Don't be charmed by its conniving countenance! It'll con a crystal from you!
        HERE_WHERE                                                              = 13440,  -- Here where?
        GIVE_SHINY_ROCK_SHIIINY_SHIIIIIINY                                      = 13441,  -- Give shiny rock! Shiiiny. Shiiiiiiny!
        YOU_GIVE_STONE_LOVE_YOU_LOOOVE_LOOOOOOVE                                = 13442,  -- You give [hot/dirty/wet/sparkly/cold/windy/bright/dark/many/big] stone! Love you! Looove! Loooooove!
        HAPPY_MUCH_HAPPY_FOR_YOU_YOOOU                                          = 13443,  -- Happy! Much happy! For you! Yooou!
        I_HAVE_STILL_HAVE_NO_NEED_MORE                                          = 13444,  -- I have! Still have! No need more!
        HEY_YOU_THERE_I_VE_GOT_A_PROPOSITION                                    = 13445,  -- Hey! You there! I've got a proposition of sorts for [a fresh-faced/an able-bodied/a world-class] adventurer such as yourself!
        YOU_CAN_CALL_ME_CLARION_STAR_I_VE                                       = 13446,  -- You can call me Clarion Star. I've come from Jeuno, the lovely city in the northeast that connects the Quon and Mindartia continents.
        SPECIFICALLY_I_M_A_REPRESENTATIVE_OF_SORTS_FROM                         = 13447,  -- Specifically, I'm a representative of sorts from the Jeuno Institute of Magical Studies. You could call me a headhunter!
        BWAHAHA_AND_THE_HEADS_I_AM_HUNTING_TODAY                                = 13448,  -- Bwahaha! And the heads I am hunting today are those of bright-eyed explorers like yourself!
        SO_HERE_S_THE_DEAL_NOT_TOO_LONG                                         = 13449,  -- So here's the deal. Not too long ago, the institute held an international symposium of sorts, at which we announced the development of a fascinatingly useful new type of magic.
        WE_MADE_IT_AVAILABLE_FOR_EVERYONE_TO_UTILIZE                            = 13450,  -- We made it available for everyone to utilize, and so we are trying it out here in Bastok and other places throughout Vana'diel.
        WE_VE_CHOSEN_TO_CALL_THE_NEW_MAGIC                                      = 13451,  -- We've chosen to call the new magic Trust, and as an official delegate of the institute, I want adventurers of your caliber to be the lucky first participants.
        SO_WHAT_ABOUT_IT_WANT_TO_TRY_IT                                         = 13452,  -- So? What about it? Want to try it out?
        TRY_OUT_THE_NEW_MAGIC_WHAT_HAVE_I                                       = 13453,  -- Try out the new magic? What have I got to lose? Magic scares me.
        AN_ADVENTURER_OF_SORTS_SCARED_OF_MAGIC_PFFFT                            = 13454,  -- An adventurer of sorts scared of magic? Pffft. Your loss, bud.
        THAT_S_THE_KIND_OF_SPUNK_I_LIKE                                         = 13455,  -- That's the kind of spunk I like!
        YOU_RE_SURELY_AWARE_THAT_BASTOK_IS_NO                                   = 13456,  -- You're surely aware that Bastok is no stranger to developing new technologies, and as such Cid and the Mythril Musketeers are conducting research of sorts into the application of this new magic.
        YOU_KNOW_HOW_THEY_ARE_ALWAYS_AT_ODDS                                    = 13457,  -- You know how they are--always at odds with the Beastman Confederate. They think that Trust might be able to help bolster their forces, they say.
        HOWEVER_NOT_JUST_ANYONE_CAN_USE_TRUST                                   = 13458,  -- However! Not just anyone can use Trust.
        AS_YOU_CAN_IMAGINE_THE_INSTITUTE_IS_THUS                                = 13459,  -- As you can imagine, the institute is thus collecting data of sorts in San d'Oria and Windurst, too, trying to get as many people as possible to participate.
        IT_SHOULD_COME_AS_NO_SURPRISE_THEN_THAT                                 = 13460,  -- It should come as no surprise, then, that we have other representatives in those two nations. If you'd rather head over there, then we've got nothing more to discuss...
        BUT_I_M_SURE_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_HERE                                = 13461,  -- But I'm sure the Mythril Musketeers here would appreciate any help you could give 'em.
        LET_S_CUT_TO_THE_QUICK_HELPING_THEM                                     = 13462,  -- Let's cut to the quick. Helping them earns you the aid of a powerful warrior of sorts, which can only help you in your travels.
        ASSIST_IN_TRUST_ENDEAVORS_IN_BASTOK_OF_COURSE                           = 13463,  -- Assist in Trust endeavors in Bastok? Of course. No, thank you.
        IF_YOU_RE_DEAD_SET_ON_GOING_ELSEWHERE                                   = 13464,  -- If you're dead set on going elsewhere, I can't stop you...but I'm right here, and surely you'd rather not take a long journey.
        BWAHAHA_PERFECT_RESPONSE                                                = 13465,  -- Bwahaha! Perfect response!
        LET_S_GET_RIGHT_TO_IT_BEFORE_WE                                         = 13466,  -- [If that's the case,/Okay! So] let's get right to it. Before we go any further, let me give you this.
        YOUR_FIRST_TASK_OF_SORTS_IS_TO_SPEAK                                    = 13467,  -- Your first task of sorts is to speak with Naji of the Mythril Musketeers, in the Metalworks. He can guide you further.
        DO_YOU_KNOW_WHERE_IT_IS_JUST_HEAD                                       = 13468,  -- Do you know where it is? Just head up the staircase behind me and cross the bridge to the west. Someone in the markets just past there can guide you further.
        TAKE_THE_LIFT_UP_TO_THE_SECOND_FLOOR                                    = 13469,  -- Take the lift up to the second floor, where you'll find him waiting by the staircase that leads to the president's office. No one across the land is as faithful or skilled a guard as he.
        HOW_ARE_YOU_FINDING_THOSE_ALTER_EGOS_NEED                               = 13470,  -- How are you finding those alter egos? Need an explanation of sorts as to how they work?
        INQUIRE_ABOUT_WHAT_WHAT_TRUST_IS_WHAT_HAPPENS                           = 13471,  -- Inquire about what? What Trust is. What happens when one uses Trust. How to learn new Trust spells. Whereabouts of Trust participants. Nothing at the moment.
        TRUST_IS_A_NEW_CATEGORY_OF_MAGIC_DEVELOPED                              = 13472,  -- Trust is a new category of magic developed and announced by the Jeuno Institute for Magical Studies.
        THOUGH_IT_IS_A_MAGIC_OF_SORTS_UNLIKE                                    = 13473,  -- Though it is a magic of sorts, unlike ordinary spells it does not require mana. Instead, it draws on the power of trust, friendship, and brotherly/sisterly] love.
        FRIENDSHIP_OF_COURSE_CROSSES_ALL_BOUNDARIES_SO_TRUST                    = 13474,  -- Friendship, of course, crosses all boundaries, so Trust magic can be used regardless of your job.
        BUT_FOR_THE_LOVE_OF_ALL_THAT_IS                                         = 13475,  -- But for the love of all that is holy, don't go around bonding with alter egos in cities. It'll confuse everyone.
        USING_TRUST_MAGIC_CALLS_FORTH_AN_ALTER_EGO                              = 13476,  -- Using Trust magic calls forth an alter ego of someone you have formed a strong personal bond with.
        THEY_SAY_FRIENDSHIPS_WORK_BEST_AS_A_RELATIONSHIP                        = 13477,  -- They say friendships work best as a relationship between equals. Thus, the alter ego is only as strong as the person who willed it into existence.
        THE_ALTER_EGO_WILL_GLADLY_FIGHT_BY_YOUR                                 = 13478,  -- The alter ego will gladly fight by your side, but you will be unable to issue it direct orders.
        RESEARCH_OF_SORTS_IS_ONGOING_BUT_IT_MIGHT                               = 13479,  -- Research of sorts is ongoing, but it might take a while for any concrete progress to be made.
        WHEN_YOU_WISH_TO_RELEASE_AN_ALTER_EGO                                   = 13480,  -- When you wish to release an alter ego from service, you only need speak to it.
        IT_GOES_WITHOUT_SAYING_THAT_IF_AN_ALTER                                 = 13481,  -- It goes without saying that if an alter ego falls in battle, it will vanish into thin air. But don't fret--you can summon it again once a certain period of time has passed.
        TRUST_MAGIC_IS_QUITE_APTLY_NAMED_IT_CALLS                               = 13482,  -- Trust magic is quite aptly named. It calls forth an alter ego of sorts using the power of trust, friendship, and brotherly/sisterly] love.
        TO_EMPLOY_ITS_POWERS_YOU_MUST_FIRST_FIND                                = 13483,  -- To employ its powers, you must first find and befriend one who is allowed to harness them.
        IF_THEY_DO_NOT_LISTEN_TO_YOUR_REQUEST                                   = 13484,  -- If they do not listen to your request, then perhaps they don't think highly enough of you. Get the town talking about your deeds and I'm sure they'll give you another chance. If they still won't listen--well, you just come back to me.
        OF_COURSE_THEY_STILL_MIGHT_NOT_WANT_TO                                  = 13485,  -- Of course, they still might not want to be friends. Maybe you're like me and doomed to be forever alone! Bwahaha! <Sob>
        OH_HO_THERE_IS_ANOTHER_WAY_TO_UTILIZE                                   = 13486,  -- Oh ho[/, I almost forgot]! There is another way to utilize this magic. There are ongoing investigations of sorts into how to call forth an alter ego without directly meeting the person.
        IT_TAKES_A_LITTLE_SOMETHING_SPECIAL_BUT_IF                              = 13487,  -- It takes a little something special, but if you find a scroll with this exceptional ability, all you need do is give it to me.
        HANG_ON_JUST_A_TICK_LET_S_TAKE                                          = 13488,  -- Hang on just a tick. Let's take a look...
